  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They suffered from blood poisoning, which was not treated, and then they died.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The young woman was asked, do you see anyone in this courtroom who has performed this experiment on you?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she pointed to Herta Oberheuser.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Herta Oberheuser had absolutely no-- a blank expression on her face, like this had nothing whatsoever to do with her.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She subsequently was sentenced to 20 years in prison, got out after 10 years, and practiced as a pediatrician, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] which I find just almost incredible.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The purpose for that experiment was because the Nazis rationalized why they were doing these awful experiments was that soldiers get wounded and lie someplace in the field and dirt is in their wounds and they lie there for a while before they treat it and it becomes infected and what happens?",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That's true.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But you know, if indeed, the wound was later on cleaned out and sewn up and then began to fester or get-- become infected, it would be opened up to see what's wrong.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And if there was something, some foreign object left inside, you remove it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You don't-- didn't have to conduct those experiments.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And you know, there were many, many other horrible experiments that were conducted, hypothermia experiments, high altitude tests, malaria, I mean, just any number of tests.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And each one the Nazis rationalized why they conducted them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't see you being--",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
